data-triple-N3.o: "This article is about railroad equipment. For other cars, see Automobile and wiktionary definition of passenger car. A passenger car (known as a coach or carriage in the UK, and also known as a bogie in India) is a piece of railway rolling stock that is designed to carry passengers. The term passenger car can also be associated with a sleeping car, baggage, dining, railway post office and prisoner transport cars."@en
